<a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarr" target="_blank">Erollisi Marr</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukhalendor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Khalendor</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.geocities.com/khalendor/mage3.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#333333>(7/23/02 4:43:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1283.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Blazing Wand</span><hr size=1> I camped a level 2 ranger at the zone to KK with EB and amazingly the track reaches all the way to Phinny.  I log on a couple times a day to see if he is up.  While I have seen him up, I haven't tackled him yet but I know it will be easy to do so.<br>
<br>
Oh, and I talked to a mage yesterday that sent a necro down to dot Undertow and then just coh'd the necro back to the zone.  Undertow warped to the zone with 2 sea horses and they easily took them with a necro, shammy, ranger and mage (all in the low 50's).  Undertow did drop the wand.<br>
<br>
Sounds like it may be easier to convince people to go to KK if they know they don't have to leave the zone.<br>
<br>
Anyway, just a thought. I think I will try it. <p><img src=http://a5.cpimg.com/image/AD/05/10888365-0078-00E1011E-.jpg"border=0"<br>
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=253526>Inspect Me</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uyenillenin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yenil Lenin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#333333>(7/23/02 4:52:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1283.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Blazing Wand</span><hr size=1> Something else, when I was lvl 52 me and my wife (51 enchanter at the time) took out Undertow and his friends.  We invis'd up and moved in to clear the trash out outside his temple.  Then pulled his guards.  On undertow she kept rune up on my pet and I chain nuked once pet had decent aggro.  Fight didn't last long, only thing was timing due to repops.  Needed to be inside the temple below undertow medding before the fish outside repop.  I'm thinking two mages could do this and have heard about mage/cleric combos.  I had a druid check on undertow every few days and sometimes every day until he was up for over a month. <p>Yenil Lenin<br>
55 Magician<br>
Leader of <a href="http://www.orderoftheblacksword.com" target="_blank">Order of the Black Sword</a><br>
Council of <a
href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarrfederation" target="_blank">The United Federation</a><br>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=146640" target="_blank">Yenil's Stuff</a><br>
<a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarr" target="_blank">Erollisi Marr</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uharrije.showPublicProfile?language=EN>harrije</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 260<br> <font color=#333333>(7/23/02 8:24:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1283.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Blazing Wand</span><hr size=1> In terms of X-Y coordinates, Kedge is very compact. That's why a low-level tracker has such good luck finding the named when they are up.<br>
<br>
So far as I know, you can multiquest the blazing wand. The only downside is the Fire NPC is in a dangerous spot and apparantly gets eaten by dragons a lot, so it's tricky to find him up and get the turn-in done before he or you die.<br>
<br>
But your best bet to get him killed is to find a couple of druid friends who need the corrupted seahorse, and make a day of it down in the temple/caves area. Do Undertow/PH first, then do seahorses ad infinitum, then eight hours later do Undertow again. He's not really that rare a spawn other than the obnoxious spawn time. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uognoh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>oGnOh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(7/24/02 9:53:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1283.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Blazing Wand</span><hr size=1> Undertow is on 8 hour spawn time but skips spawns, or atleast that's what i've seen in all my hours in Kedge.  He's actually much more common than the PH, a swirlspine seahorse (which also sees invis and ripped me apart before I could gate even with full raid buffs).  Just park a ranger in there and check a couple of times a day.  Or you can just bind there and live in Kedge like me.<br>
<br>
And to answer your question:  Yes, the whole Mage epic is MQable.<br>
